tickets.summary: When a user session expires, the dashboard throws a 500 error instead of redirecting the user to the login page.
tickets.description:
Steps to Reproduce

Login successfully

Stay idle for 30+ minutes

Refresh /dashboard

Expected Result

User is redirected to /login with “Session expired” message.

Actual Result

HTTP 500 error shown on dashboard.

Acceptance Criteria

Session expiry intercepted

Redirect instead of crash

Error logged at WARN level only
tickets.logs:
[ERROR] 2026-01-19 14:33:12 AuthMiddleware
TokenExpiredError: JWT expired at 2026-01-19T14:00:00Z

[ERROR] DashboardController
Unhandled exception while fetching user context

comments.message: AI Resolution worked. Marking as done.
Re-opening the ticket for verification. Now in Progress

tickets.rca: The AuthMiddleware fails to catch the 'TokenExpiredError' thrown by the JWT verification library. When a user's session expires, this exception is propagated as an unhandled error to the DashboardController and the global error handler, resulting in a generic 500 Internal Server Error instead of a controlled redirect. Additionally, the current implementation logs this routine session expiry as an ERROR rather than a WARN level event.
